				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I should point out to you that this is only good for "Normal" sprite overflow emulation. "Correct" sprite overflow emulation is much, much stranger, due to a <strong>flaw in the PPU hardware</strong> which causes it to, once exactly 8 sprites have been found, evaluate sprite TILE, FLAGS, and X-coordinate as though they were Y coordinates. More details can be found in the wiki.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Quietust, QMT Productions
<br />P.S. If you don't get this note, let me know and I'll write you another.</div>
