					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Bigfoot, The Three Stooges, and Spy vs. Spy didn't use the max sprites flag for their split-screen effects (I'm assuming they used sprite hit). I'll have to try some of the more obscure Codemasters games.
<br />
<br />I played around a bit with the odd PPU search pattern for the 9th sprite. It seems that the flag isn't even useful as a way to find if any sprites were (partially) hidden due to exceeding the maximum per scanline. It doesn't even seem reliable as a secondary equivalent to sprite 0 hit for finding when a particular scanline is hit, since it might get set on any scanline with 8 sprites and particular tile/attribute/x values that the search pattern looks at. It would work for marking the end of a status display, since there you can easily ensure that there are always 7 or less sprites per scanline.</div>

