						<div class="postbody">Just tested them again and none write to sprite memory mid-frame. I also tested Stunt Kids, another one with split-screen scrolling. I'm going to verify that you can actually rewrite sprites mid-frame, then perhaps have my tool scan all 3500+ ROMs for instances of this.
<br />
<br />What's the significance of this? The algorithm works perfectly well if sprite RAM is rewritten mid-frame, it just needs to 1) set the max sprites flag if that event already occurred, and 2) recalculate the sprites per line for the remaining scanlines.</div>

